HEADWORD: Knight bachelor
<hw>Knight" bach"e*lor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Knights
bachelors</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A knight of the most ancient,
but lowest, order of English knights, and not a member of any order of
chivalry. See <er>Bachelor</er>, 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

